HEADWORD: Stilton
<hw>Stil"ton</hw> }</mhw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A peculiarly flavored
unpressed cheese made from milk with cream added; -- so called from the
village or parish of <etsep>Stilton</etsep>, England, where it was
originally made. It is very rich in fat.</def></p>

<p><q>Thus, in the outset he was gastronomic; discussed the dinner from
the soup to the <qex>stilton</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>C.
Lever.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stilty</ent>⟦br⟧
